4)Write a program to concatenate two Strings eg- “hello” and “world” and
check if the result of concatenation equals “helloworld” (using.equals() and ==).
Trim the strings to get the two strings back.
Program:-
class concat{
public static void main(String args[]){
String s1=new String("Aditi");
String s2=new String(" Patil");
String s3=new String("Aditi Patil");
String s4=s1.concat(s2);
System.out.println(s4);
if(s3.equals(s4)){
System.out.println("s3 and s4 are equal by .equals() method");
}
else{
System.out.println("s3 and s4 are not equal by .equals() method");
}
if(s3==s4){
System.out.println("s3 and s4 are equal by equality operator");
}
else{
System.out.println("s3 and s4 are not equal by equality operator");
}
System.out.println(s4.substring(0,s1.length()));
System.out.println(s4.substring(s1.length()));
}
}
